WEBVTT

00:04.104 --> 00:07.040
(Doorbell rings)

00:07.040 --> 00:10.110
(Knocks on door)

00:12.112 --> 00:16.049
Hi. Kate Scott.
"Scandalous magazine."

00:16.049 --> 00:18.051
Mm. The Darlings aren't home.

00:18.051 --> 00:20.053
Oh, well, um... (Laughs)

00:20.053 --> 00:22.122
Do you know
when they might be back?

00:22.122 --> 00:24.124
The Darlings are away
for Thanksgiving.

00:24.124 --> 00:26.059
Well, I am doing

00:26.059 --> 00:28.061
a 2,000-word exposÃ©
on the family and--

00:28.061 --> 00:31.064
I'm familiar with your column.
"Red carpet confidential."

00:31.064 --> 00:33.066
Not a fan?
Come on, what have you got,

00:33.066 --> 00:36.036
a couple of shots of Karen
sunbathing topless in Ibiza?

00:36.036 --> 00:40.007
Print 'em.
Oh, actually, this is not
a puff piece.

00:40.007 --> 00:41.074
And if I wanted

00:41.074 --> 00:44.011
to print pictures
of Karen Darling's ya-yas,

00:44.011 --> 00:46.013
I wouldn't have to look hard.

00:46.013 --> 00:48.081
No, I'm doing a piece
about family betrayal,

00:48.081 --> 00:50.117
criminal cover-ups
and murder.

00:50.117 --> 00:52.085
I'm just the chauffeur.

00:52.085 --> 00:54.087
Which means you have
a front-row seat

00:54.087 --> 00:56.089
for every
sordid Darling debacle.

00:56.089 --> 00:58.091
I drive the car.
I don't see much.

00:58.091 --> 01:01.061
That's not
what I hear, Clark.

01:01.061 --> 01:04.131
Look, I go to press
in six hours.

01:04.131 --> 01:07.000
It's part of
our holiday special issue.

01:07.000 --> 01:10.037
I just want to fact-check
my story.

01:10.037 --> 01:12.105
Or the I can run
the piece as is.

01:12.105 --> 01:15.075
It's your choice.

01:18.078 --> 01:20.013
Wow.

01:20.013 --> 01:22.049
I always wondered
what this place looked like.

01:22.049 --> 01:24.051
It's just a family home.

01:24.051 --> 01:26.053
So was versailles.

01:33.026 --> 01:34.094
So...

01:34.094 --> 01:36.096
How long
is this gonna take?

01:36.096 --> 01:40.133
20 minutes.
An hour tops.

01:40.133 --> 01:44.104
Okay, first question--
I have information

01:44.104 --> 01:47.107
that before Letitia was charged
with the murder of Dutch George,

01:47.107 --> 01:50.077
the police were investigating
somebody else.

01:50.077 --> 01:53.046
Well, they should've stayed
focused on that person,

01:53.046 --> 01:56.083
because, as you know,
Mrs. Darling was found innocent.

01:56.083 --> 01:59.019
Who is this suspect?

01:59.019 --> 02:02.055
Her husband, your boss--
Tripp Darling.

02:02.055 --> 02:05.025
Mr. Darling was never
under investigation

02:05.025 --> 02:07.027
for the murder
of Dutch George.

02:07.027 --> 02:09.128
Check your sources.
So you're denying

02:09.128 --> 02:13.066
that when Patrick Darling
was the Attorney General...
Okay, whoa. Wait a second.

02:13.066 --> 02:16.103
Of the state of New York, he
investigated his own father...
Okay, okay.

02:16.103 --> 02:20.007
Before that investigation
mysteriously went away?
You're half right.

02:20.007 --> 02:23.043
A while back, Patrick was
going after his father,

02:23.043 --> 02:26.013
but it didn't have anything
to do with Dutch's murder.

02:26.013 --> 02:28.015
(Clark)
This whole thing started

02:28.015 --> 02:30.117
when Tripp received
an unexpected visitor.

02:30.117 --> 02:32.119
Mr. Tripp Darling?
Yeah.

02:32.119 --> 02:35.088
You been served.
(Man) Let's go.

02:35.088 --> 02:37.124
What's that?

02:37.124 --> 02:41.028
Well, it's a subpoena from
the Attorney General's office,

02:41.028 --> 02:43.030
signed by Patrick,
calling you to testify

02:43.030 --> 02:45.065
in the Fantini brothers case.

02:45.065 --> 02:47.067
Tripp needed
that subpoena to go away.

02:47.067 --> 02:49.069
The fact that the investigation

02:49.069 --> 02:51.071
was being brought
by Tripp's son Patrick

02:51.071 --> 02:53.073
and that the two hadn't exactly
been getting along

02:53.073 --> 02:55.108
made things
even more complicated.

02:55.108 --> 02:57.110
(Nick) I can try to quash it.

02:57.110 --> 02:59.079
No,
trying is not good enough.

02:59.079 --> 03:01.081
It is imperative
that the two of you

03:01.081 --> 03:04.117
figure out a way to make sure
that I am not compelled

03:04.117 --> 03:07.120
to walk into that courtroom.
Why don't you want
to testify?

03:07.120 --> 03:10.057
They're mobsters, Brian.
The Fantini brothers
have a long

03:10.057 --> 03:12.059
and tempestuous history
with us.

03:12.059 --> 03:14.027
Our professional dealings
with them

03:14.027 --> 03:16.029
have always been
above board,

03:16.029 --> 03:18.031
ethically pristine.

03:18.031 --> 03:20.033
But if am called
to bear witness,

03:20.033 --> 03:22.035
they'll do everything
in their power

03:22.035 --> 03:25.105
to make the court believe that
all of their foul corruption

03:25.105 --> 03:27.074
stems from us.

03:27.074 --> 03:29.009
Regrettably...

03:29.009 --> 03:31.044
Patrick knows this, too.

03:31.044 --> 03:33.113
I'll take care of it.

03:33.113 --> 03:36.016
Well... take care of it.

03:36.016 --> 03:39.019
So Nick and Brian
went to see Patrick,

03:39.019 --> 03:41.054
you know, to try and keep
this misunderstanding

03:41.054 --> 03:43.056
within the family.

03:43.056 --> 03:44.124
Patrick, as Attorney General,

03:44.124 --> 03:47.060
it's within your power to offer
the Fantini brothers a deal.

03:47.060 --> 03:49.062
Your office gets
an easy conviction,

03:49.062 --> 03:51.031
and it saves taxpayers
some money

03:51.031 --> 03:54.034
on what would be a lengthy
and messy trial--case closed.

03:54.034 --> 03:56.069
I already offered
the Fantini brothers

03:56.069 --> 03:59.106
a very reasonable plea deal,
and they wouldn't take it.
Well, then drop the case,
dumb-ass.

03:59.106 --> 04:03.010
Hey, what happened
to hanging back?
What happened
to getting the job done?

04:03.010 --> 04:05.078
Brian, asking me
to drop the case

04:05.078 --> 04:08.015
is an obstruction of justice.
That's a felony.

04:08.015 --> 04:11.018
Uh, surely Nick must have
explained that to you already.

04:11.018 --> 04:14.087
Unless he's
in on the plan, too.

04:14.087 --> 04:17.024
My, how, uh,
things have changed.

04:17.024 --> 04:19.125
Hey, would you drop
the prissy tone?

04:19.125 --> 04:22.029
We're talking about
your father.

04:22.029 --> 04:24.064
I could talk like
Clint Eastwood if you like,

04:24.064 --> 04:26.033
but my hands are tied.

04:26.033 --> 04:28.101
The Fantini brothers
wanted the big show,

04:28.101 --> 04:31.038
and I'm just, uh,
bringing the popcorn.
Patrick, we all know

04:31.038 --> 04:33.106
that the only reason you're
going after the Fantini brothers

04:33.106 --> 04:36.009
is to attack Tripp.
Uh, listen, gentlemen,
thanks for coming.

04:36.009 --> 04:38.078
If you'll excuse me, I've gotta
get back to my career

04:38.078 --> 04:40.047
of fighting crime.

04:40.047 --> 04:42.082
Patrick, this isn't over.

04:42.082 --> 04:45.018
Really? (Chuckles)

04:45.018 --> 04:47.020
Seems like it is.

04:47.020 --> 04:49.056
After striking out
with Patrick,

04:49.056 --> 04:51.058
Nick wanted to go
through channels.

04:51.058 --> 04:55.028
Brian chose
a... less diplomatic approach.

04:55.028 --> 04:56.096
I-I just, I, uh--

04:56.096 --> 04:58.031
let me guess.
Brian's here.

04:58.031 --> 05:00.067
Should I send him in?
Nice work, Daisy.

05:00.067 --> 05:02.069
You got it.
Look, I have called
the governor's office,

05:02.069 --> 05:03.136
I am waiting to hear

05:03.136 --> 05:06.039
on a judge's ruling on
an injunction, and right now,

05:06.039 --> 05:08.075
I have to get home and see
my daughter for dinner, okay?
Well, that must be nice.

05:08.075 --> 05:11.011
Meaning?
To accomplish
absolutely nothing

05:11.011 --> 05:13.080
and then go home
with so much friggin' bacon.

05:13.080 --> 05:16.083
What do you want
from me, Brian?
I want you to be half the guy
Tripp thinks you are

05:16.083 --> 05:18.118
and get something done.
I just said I'm on it.

05:18.118 --> 05:21.021
No, you know what?
I'm on it.
What does that mean?

05:21.021 --> 05:22.089
You're never gonna get Patrick

05:22.089 --> 05:24.091
or anybody else
to dismiss this case.

05:24.091 --> 05:27.027
The papers have made too much
of a big deal out of it,

05:27.027 --> 05:30.030
and Patrick is never
gonna back down.
Well, you're right about that,
but what are you gonna do?

05:30.030 --> 05:32.099
I'm gonna go down to Jersey,
talk to these Fantini brothers,

05:32.099 --> 05:35.068
and maybe get 'em
to make a deal.
These guys are connected,
Brian. They're dangerous.

05:35.068 --> 05:37.070
You're gonna walk in there
and say what?

05:37.070 --> 05:40.073
I'm Brian Darling, paisan,
and this is how it's gonna be.

05:40.073 --> 05:44.011
How the hell
were you ever a minister?
You ever read the Bible?

05:44.011 --> 05:48.015
It's full of aggravating people
that get things done.

05:48.015 --> 05:50.017
Check it out.

05:50.017 --> 05:54.021
I wish I could tell you
that Brian was all talk,

05:54.021 --> 05:57.090
but when that kid
gets an idea in his head...

05:57.090 --> 06:01.094
(Billy Squiers
everybody wants you playing)

06:01.094 --> 06:04.031
? You see em coming at you
every night ?

06:04.031 --> 06:05.098
Sorry to keep you waiting,
padre.

06:05.098 --> 06:07.067
That's ex-padre.

06:07.067 --> 06:10.070
You know, I don't even know
if this is allowed.

06:10.070 --> 06:12.072
The son of a witness,
the brother of Patrick Darling

06:12.072 --> 06:14.107
talking to defendants?

06:14.107 --> 06:17.010
All of a sudden you're
a stickler for the rules?

06:17.010 --> 06:19.012
Give me a break.
So what do you want?

06:19.012 --> 06:21.081
I know you didn't come
all the way to Jersey

06:21.081 --> 06:24.084
just to catch a glimpse
of some of that.
I want you to make a deal.

06:24.084 --> 06:27.020
Take a suspended sentence
or something,

06:27.020 --> 06:29.089
and make this case go away.
Why would we do that?

06:29.089 --> 06:31.091
Because if you don't,
you just might end up

06:31.091 --> 06:33.093
rotting away in prison
where you both friggin' belong.

06:33.093 --> 06:35.095
Why don't you let
your brother--little paddy--

06:35.095 --> 06:37.998
worry about such stuff, huh?

06:37.998 --> 06:41.101
Look, we can handle this
one of two ways.

06:41.101 --> 06:44.104
You take a deal, or I can call
my brother and make sure

06:44.104 --> 06:48.008
that you both go to jail
for a long, long time.

06:48.008 --> 06:49.042
